// Question Manager
// Manages pending questions and response history per collab session, used to relay MCP questions to the UI.

Only one question can be pending per session at a time; a new question replaces the previous one.
A singleton instance (questionManager) is exported for convenience.

FUNCTION receiveQuestion(sessionName, question) -> void
  Validate that sessionName and question (with id and text) are non-empty.
  Store the question as the pending question for the session, replacing any prior pending question.

---

FUNCTION receiveResponse(sessionName, response) -> boolean
  Validate inputs. Look up the pending question for the session.
  IF no pending question exists or its id does not match response.questionId, return false.
  Move the question to history and remove it from pending. Return true.

---

FUNCTION dismissQuestion(sessionName) -> boolean
  Remove the pending question for the session without recording a response.
  Return true if a question was dismissed, false if none was pending.

---

FUNCTION getQuestion(sessionName) -> Question | null
  Return the current pending question for the session, or null if none.

---

FUNCTION getHistory(sessionName) -> QuestionResponse[]
  Return the list of responded questions for the session, or an empty array.

---

FUNCTION clearHistory(sessionName) -> boolean
  Delete the history for the session. Return true if history existed, false if not.

---

FUNCTION clearSession(sessionName) -> void
  Remove both the pending question and full history for the session. Used during session cleanup.

---

FUNCTION getPendingSessionNames() -> string[]
  Return the list of all session names that currently have a pending question.

---

FUNCTION getHistorySessions() -> string[]
  Return the list of all session names that have question history.

---

FUNCTION hasPendingQuestion(sessionName) -> boolean
  Return true if the session has an unanswered pending question.
